Product description

Our Story

CaseBot, a premium series brought to you by Fintie!

How we got our start?

Founded in Columbus Ohio, Fintie LLC brings you stylish and high quality products and accessories for home furnishing. We have been in the home furnishing product business for over 13 years and directly manufacture most of the popular products we sell.

What makes our product unique?

We believe customers are looking for reasonably priced products but without any sacrifice on quality. Our aim is to reach every single customer that falls into this group with our quality products. Our direct sales model without a middleman allows us to pass significant savings to our customers.

Why we love what we do?

Since we control our own production runs, we take great pride in our ability to constantly excite our customers with new product designs and styles. Our reliable customer support team is here to help you with any questions you have about your purchase or the products we offer.

Our thermostat wall plate can covers up the previous hole or mark.

NOTE: PLEAES CHECK YOUR THERMOSTAT MODEL BEFORE PURCHASING

Fit Module:

Compatible with Amazon Smart Thermostat 2021 release

  • Hurricane Target
    4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Installed 2-3 years later, lol.
    Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
    Color: White
    So yeah. It took a while to install. Long story but bought this for my parents. Then dad died. Then we found out they didnt have a control wire. Then the HVAC guy didnt want to hook it up for us because he was just there to do basic maintenance. Their old... See more
    So yeah. It took a while to install. Long story but bought this for my parents. Then dad died. Then we found out they didnt have a control wire. Then the HVAC guy didnt want to hook it up for us because he was just there to do basic maintenance.

    Their old thermostat ran on batteries and didnt automatically heat and cool within a range so they were regularly switching it back and forth and raising/lowering the temp.

    So it sat until yesterday when I decided to just figure it out for myself. Was done in 2 hours. It should not have taken that long but me and 220v circuits do not get along.

    That time was mostly me inside the HVAC figuring out how to read the transformer to find where the 24vac wires went.

    Took me the longest to figure out where to connect the control wire because their HVAC has no control board or obvious C wire connector. Enter YouTube, an multimeter, and electrical engineering 101 for me.

    Eventually, I was able to trace the step down transformer lines and figure out which was the constant 24vac hot vs return/neutral to complete the circuit. They changed colors on me due to however/whoever installed it.

    After figuring that out the setup was really simple and straightforward.
    Helpful
